    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but that's the thing, that's what everyone says. \"it gets better\" or \"you can rebuild.\" it's just such a hollow lie. when you've been broken so many times, the \"repair\" just feels like more patching up parts that shouldn't even be there. i don't want to be \"rebuilt.\" i just feel like there's no point in even trying to mend something that's fundamentally just... ruined. don't you think some things are just meant to stay broken?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I understand that it feels like you're trapped in a cycle of brokenness, but sometimes, even the most damaged parts can find a way to function again. It's not about being \"rebuilt\" or pretending everything is okay. It's about finding a way to live with what you have, even if it's not perfect. Sometimes, the most broken pieces can create something new and unexpected. Maybe it's time to explore that possibility, even if it feels impossible right now.",
      "source": "target",
